cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image classification. The use of deep learning and convolution neural networks also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The attention-based multiple instance pooling and loss minimization techniques used in the proposed method suggest that it could also belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of aerial images suggests that it could belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as well.
